0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "The Maple commands \+
" }{TEXT 266 16 "expand, simplify" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 267 6 "n
ormal" }{TEXT -1 483 " can be use to rearrange, manipulate and simplif
y (cancel common factors) algebraic sums, products and quotients of ra
tional expressions.   When a rational expression is normalized, any co
mmon factors are cancelled.  Go back to each of your calculations of e
., f., g., h. and i. and add to each line a command to expand the calc
ulation, to normalize the calculation, to simplify the calculation and
 both expand and normalize the calculation.  E.g., the line for e. wou
ld change from:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "F*H/G;" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 2 "to" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 99 "F*H/G; expand(F*H/G); normal
